104 /// This function attempts to replace V with a simpler value based on the
105 /// demanded bits. When this function is called, it is known that only the bits
106 /// set in DemandedMask of the result of V are ever used downstream.
107 /// Consequently, depending on the mask and V, it may be possible to replace V
108 /// with a constant or one of its operands. In such cases, this function does
109 /// the replacement and returns true. In all other cases, it returns false after
110 /// analyzing the expression and setting KnownOne and known to be one in the
111 /// expression. Known.Zero contains all the bits that are known to be zero in
112 /// the expression. These are provided to potentially allow the caller (which
